DESCRIPTION:How has the most meme’able\, memorable and mischievous animal known to man been represented across art history in the subcontinent?\n\nJoin curator Khushi Bansal as she explores the many lives of the Indian cat—appearing in paintings\, sculptures\, matchbox covers\, artist sketchbooks\, and beyond.\n\nThis event is part of the closing weekend celebrations for The Many Lives of the Cat.
DTEND:20260329T100000Z
DTSTART:20260329T090000Z
SUMMARY:Curator’s POV
