BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Website-cover-images-new-2026-03-06T095723.726.png
CATEGORIES:Workshops,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260306T044534Z
DESCRIPTION:Image Credits: Sanchita Jain\nJoin us for a lively conversation about cats\, their histories\, myths\, and personalities. Exploring two books on Indian cats\, B. N. Goswamy's The Indian Cat and Olliewanders\, you can swap stories\, challenge common misconceptions\, and celebrate the surprising complexity of our feline companions.\n\nExpect good conversation\, plenty of colour\, and a "mosaic of many cats" who may look suspiciously like their humans\, especially for anyone who suspects they might\, spiritually\, be a cat.\n\nThis event is part of the closing weekend celebrations for The Many Lives of the Cat.
DTEND:20260328T103000Z
DTSTART:20260328T090000Z
SUMMARY:Miniature to Mischief
